<p>For anisotropic systems Poisson’s ratio changes with the direction of measurement and may take any value between minus and plus infinity [
 <xref rid="B18-materials-12-00700" ref-type="bibr">18</xref>]. A relatively recently discovered group of materials for which Poisson’s ratio takes negative values [
 <xref rid="B19-materials-12-00700" ref-type="bibr">19</xref>], the so-called 
 <italic>auxetics</italic> [
 <xref rid="B20-materials-12-00700" ref-type="bibr">20</xref>], has become the subject of intense studies, both theoretical [
